Detailed Description

This is an immutable implementation of the VOIPDataDict interface.

It provides the ability to conveniently construct it from a python dictionary.

Constructor & Destructor Documentation

BWVOIPDataDict::BWVOIPDataDict ( PyObject *  pyDict  ) 

Constructor.

Populates the data dictionary with every string:string entry in the provided python dictionary.

Member Function Documentation

bool BWVOIPDataDict::get ( unsigned int  index,
const char **  key,
const char **  value 
) const [virtual]

This function retrieves a key value pair based on a given index less than size().

The pairs need not be in any order. The intended purpose being to handle situations where the dictionary needs to be cloned into another format such as a python object.

Parameters:
index An index less than size() that uniquely identifies a key value pair.
key Output. On success this pointer will point to a string containing the key. This pointer will be left untouched on error.
value Output. On success this pointer will point to a string containing the value. This pointer will be left untouched on error.
Returns:
Returns true on success, false on failure

Implements VOIPDataDict.
